de.wwu.muggl.vm.impl.symbolic.support
Class JavaToSymbolicConversion

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.vm.impl.symbolic.support.JavaToSymbolicConversion

public class JavaToSymbolicConversion
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides static methods for the conversion of objects from java to symbolic types and the other way around. It offers both methods that directly take distinct types as well as general methods that will process various types.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-10
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

tryToSymbolic

public static de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Constant tryToSymbolic(java.lang.Object object)
Provide a symbolic constant value for the object specified. If the object cannot be converted, an exception will be thrown. Any instance of a primitive type java.lang wrapper class will be processed by this method.

Parameters:
object - The java object to convert.
Returns:
The symbolic constant.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the specified object has a type that cannot be converted to a symbolic type or is an array.

tryToJava

public static java.lang.Object tryToJava(de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Constant constant)
Provide a primitive type java.lang wrapper object for the symbolic constant specified. The only java objects resulting from this operation may be Boolean, Double, Float, Integer or Long.

Parameters:
constant - The symbolic constant to convert.
Returns:
A primitive type java.lang wrapper object for the symbolic constant specified.

tryToJava

public static java.lang.Object tryToJava(de.wwu.testtool.expressions.Constant constant,
                                         java.lang.Class<?> type)
Provide a primitive type java.lang wrapper object for the symbolic constant specified. The only java objects resulting from this operation may be Boolean, Byte, Character Double, Float, Integer, Long or Short. However, to have a Byte, Character or Short returned the type parameter has to be set explicitly and the specified constant has to be of type IntConstant.

Parameters:
constant - The symbolic constant to convert.
type - The type of the desired object. May be Byte.TYPE, Character.TYPE, Short.TYPE or null.
Returns:
A primitive type java.lang wrapper object for the symbolic constant specified.
